tip.text: Refreshing menu. Try the salmon ball salad with its interesting presentation. Hanabi Sushi for tuna tataki and foie gras lovers. Yakitori here is also excellent. Fatty tuna soup made with great dashi.
They specialise in the clay pot variant of BKT. They also have the dry variant.
If the sets don't appeal, go to the adjacent counter to choose from a whole other variety. The Nagoya chicken chop and Eringgi Sanma wrap is great! I also like the oden. Reheating available.
Good price for a whole lot of variety of fishes freshly flown in from Japan. Get them to recommend the catch of the day.

formattedAddress: 58200 Off Jalan Kuchai Lama, Kuala Lumpur

venue.name: Jo's Fish Market ジョースマケット

tip.text: Average western fare. Lamb chop tastes kinda gamy.
The most popular stall here is the Teochew noodles. The CCF stall's YTF is very big for RM1. 50 a piece. Don't eat at the new prawn mee stall. Freaking sweet.

venue.name: Restoran Master Q 老夫子美食中心

tip.text: All breakfast sets come with free black coffee, tea, or orange juice (not fresh). I recommend the big breakfast and baked eggs. Great scrambled eggs.

location.address: C-07-G, Block C Setiawalk, Persiaran Wawasan, Pusat Bandar Puchong
formattedAddress: C-07-G, Block C Setiawalk, Persiaran Wawasan, Pusat Bandar Puchong

tip.text: Tuna tataki is interesting with a side of Thai salad and topped with crispy dried shrimp. Tomyam ramen is sweet-ish. The beef was a little overdone. Soft bone chicken karaage nice but small portion.
Latte is decent. RM11.
Want tofu and cheesecake at the same time? Don't worry, order the tofu cheesecake! Excellent texture, light cheese taste with a hint of soy. Slightly sweet. Interesting dessert.
Nyonya food here has a price range near to that of Madam Kwan's. The Nasi Kerabu comes with a nice mix of fried chicken, beef rendang, chicken satay, and potato samosa.

formattedAddress: ioi city mall (Lebuh IRC, IOI Resort City)

tip.text: A place for Malay food- Nasi Campur, Nasi Ayam

formattedAddress: Kuala Lumpur, Federal Territory of Kuala Lum

tip.text: A place for pizza, booze and live music. Lunch sets available.
Loco Local is a cute stack of petite pancakes topped with salted caramel ice cream. Comes with a side of caramelized bananas, ciconut, and gula melaka. Quite delicious.
Mee goreng ayam not bad, big portion. Teh tarik also got some standard and they really make it less sweet for you. My lunch cost me RM10.20.
Always check the bill, things can get messy. Come early during weekday lunch , else it's gonna be a long wait. Lotsa ice in the drinks.

formattedAddress: Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Just a 15 minute walk from Brunei Hotel.

venue.name: Church Of Our Lady Of The Assumption (COLA)

tip.text: Good mix of Sushi at BND15: consists of salmon, tamago, surf clam, hotate, hokigai, anago and unagi. The kitchen is slow though. Mostly raw food here, the only cooked items in the kids menu.

formattedAddress: Unit 41, Grd Flr, Jln Sultan, (Jalan Sultan)

tip.text: Authentic Chinese restaurant with Cantonese speaking waitress. Interior is very Oriental and has a river view. Lunch meals here are same with other places which makes it a steal. Free tea on weekdays
Come here to dine with the locals. For some reason a whole lot of Indonesian cuisine. I tried the gurami goreng at gerai #3. Super crunchy with a great sambal terasi.
Friendly service. Fair price with big portions. Recommend to try the curry fish head and salted egg pork.
Small, modern hotel in the heart of town. Well-maintained.
Good location within vicinity of plenty of food options and shops. There's even a department store nearby.
The grilled sea bass is recommended. Portions aren't too big.
Huge variety of dishes, mostly Oriental. Quick service, perfect for lunch break. Try the butter prawns, very fragrant and fluffy egg floss. BND6.
They have lunch specials ranging from 12.90 to 19.90 that comes with a main, drink, soup and dessert. Average taste. The waiters can openly argue, scaring away potential customers.

location.address: Lot G-OS-3, Ground Floor, Faber Towers
formattedAddress: Lot G-OS-3, Ground Floor, Faber Towers

tip.text: Fuwa-fuwa us an interesting 'albino' bread loaf that is super soft. Taste-wise it is a bit saltier than usual. RM16.

You can choose from the fatties Ginjo pork at 55% to something less at 40%. In my opinion, the normal pork loin is already good enough. The cabbage still has that raw cabbage taste. Saboten SG better.

location.address: The Table, Level 4, Isetan The Japan Store KL
formattedAddress: The Table, Level 4, Isetan The Japan Store KL (Lot 10 Kuala Lumpur)

tip.text: Curry chicken is very oily, but comes with quite a number of pieces of meat and potatoes. The kopi ping is recommended.

formattedAddress: Megan Avenue II (Jalan Yap Kwan Seng)

tip.text: Nyonya steamed tilapia is good. Perfect with white rice. Buttermilk pork ribs is also recommended. However, I didn't like the pumpkin tofu. The gravy is too thick and conceals quickly.

venue.name: CST Restaurant & Bak Kut Teh (來發發肉骨茶家鄉小菜)

tip.text: YTF at RM1.50 per piece, not very big but the fish paste is excellent, springy. Homemade sauce. Nasi Lemak with chicken rendang is also nice (though it's actually fried chicken with rendang gravy)
A very quiet place to have coffee, hidden in a wing near TWG. Good selection of cakes, and they have hand brew coffee.
Curry fish fillet is too sweet but the gravy thick. Inche Kabin is also sweet, and oily. Best was stir fried okra with prawns.
A Christian-run cafe with upbeat music. Flat white is not bad. Green tea latte is a bit weird.
The spring roll is yummy, bursting with the fragrance of apple mint and shrimp. The sauce that comes with it reminded me a bit of peanut butter. Haha. Pho Ga and Pho Bo is average. Big portions.
Tried the steamed fish head signature style and superior broth clams. Average tasting but can say they don't use much MSG. Not thirsty after the meal. Parking can be a challenge.
Interesting Thai-Japanese offerings here. Like the stir-fried soba with sweet basil, but the portion was kinda small. Iced Thai Coffee is quite good, not too sickly sweet.
Guinness Bourbon float looks like a Milo dinosaur, but tastes very strong with a chocolate ice cream in the center. Love the Pisang Bakar Cheese. The banana is so fragrant with a layer of caramel.
A cosy place to have coffee and cake. They have a tea time special where you get 50% off cake, muffin, Danish with every beverage ordered.
A very authentic Sushi experience. Sit at the counter and watch the deft hands of the Sushi chef. Sushi here is glazed with soy sauce which is a first for me. Prices range from $110-420.
First neighbourhood Japanese restaurant in BK5. Kaiten sushi at 1.7 and 2.7, good for the budget conscious. Grilled Hamachi collar only 19.90. Don't expect too much, you get what you pay for.
You get a subset of Madam Kwan's menu here, minus the service charge. Value meals come with a free drink.
Tried the combination twist of Chayen and French Sea Salt Vanilla. Couldn't differentiate one from the other. RM 5.90.
A bit overrated IMHO. The clear broth is sweet-ish with rice wine. The spicy soup reminds me of Tom yum noodles. Bursting meatballs not fantastic. Mi Xian doesn't have very good texture.

venue.name: Go Noodle House 有间麵館

tip.text: Average tasting food. Seafood aglio-olio is super spicy. Such a kick. Seafood quite fresh. Waiter can be a little blur.
Not very porky soup, a bit too sweet for my liking. Big mug of white coffee for RM3.
Had a trio of rum & raisin, valrhona choc & banana pecan. Great flavours but each was +1.50. Came up to RM25 with a cone.

location.address: Avantas Residences (Lot G-3), Jalan Klang Lama
formattedAddress: Avantas Residences (Lot G-3), Jalan Klang Lama

tip.text: Average tasting chicken and duck rice. Rice kinda dry.

venue.name: Restoran Hoong Kee (洪记烧腊小食馆)

tip.text: Goodness, the iberico pork ribs are heavenly. Patatas Bravas though simple reminded me of what I had in BCN. Seafood paella has an amazing Prawn aroma. Book on weekends to avoid disappointment.

contact.facebookName: Marta's Kitchen in KL Paella and Tapas

location.address: The Signature, 3 Jalan Sri Hartamas 22, Desa Sri Hartamas
formattedAddress: The Signature, 3 Jalan Sri Hartamas 22, Desa Sri Hartamas

tip.text: Multiple ways of enjoying this delicious dry soba. Original. Add chili powder. Add their homemade vinegar that is infused with chili and kelp. Can get a dollop of rice to finish up the sauce remnants

location.address: 16,Japan radin bagus6, bandar baru, Sri petaling
formattedAddress: 16,Japan radin bagus6, bandar baru, Sri petaling

tip.text: Interesting Fusion menu. Fine dining-esque plating. Barramundi Green curry is not bad with rice that reminds me of Nasi Dagang. Beware when talking to the migrant waiters, might have some miscomm.
Essentially a drinking place with food. Food portions aren't very big. Was kinda shocked that the Thai duck salad was like a small pile of spring onions. Fish and Cheese too salty.
Cheap meat in hawker setting. Pork ribs are RM18, comes with mash and slaw. A nice long pair of ribs that you eat with plastic gloves. Messy meal. Wild Mushroom soup is not overly creamy.
This place has a symbiosis with the adjacent Super Kidz playground. Parents loiter here and you can hear noisy kids. Hazelnut latte tastes weird. Earl Grey cake is good, but a bit small.
Look for goodies in the chef's recommendations. Changes every week. Had good stewed rabbit and crispy duck. For starters, I recommend the hearty monkfish stew. Profiteroles are good to! Big portion.
Banafogatto - seriously can't taste the banana. Fluffy pancakes though. Coffee is OK.
Good ambience. Cosy. Cafe with food. Coffees are decent and relatively cheap. Tried the thick toast with ice cream. Perfect for two.

contact.facebookName: Take Eat Easy Modern Bakery & Cafe

tip.text: The grilled pork ribs here taste great, but you have to use your hands. Disposable gloves are provided. Well-seasoned. Comes with a side of sour baby romaine. End with a shot of lemon juice.
Cheap coffee. Signature Coffee not bad. ChocoBerry cake is average.
Pho Ga is good. The chicken stock is flavourful. The grilled minced meat medallions in the bun is also great. They also have an artichoke tea that I have not seen elsewhere.

location.address: The Gardens Mall (LG-203B), Lingkaran Syed Putra
formattedAddress: The Gardens Mall (LG-203B), Lingkaran Syed Putra

tip.text: Signature crabs are good. Meaty Sri Lankan crabs. Signature noodles are wantan noodles with minced meat. Not oily, good taste. Parking is limited here, but seating area is very big.

venue.name: Seremban Seafood Village 芙蓉燒蟹海鮮村

tip.text: Roasted Hazelnut Latte is quite good. Flat white is bland though. Reasonable prices.
Expensive coffees that aren't impressive. The Coffee Smith is served as espresso, americano and milk, that's supposed to be enjoyed one after another. Just a gimmick. Doesn't harmonise.
Nasi Dagang here is not bad. RM9.90. Nasi Kerabu also has lots of kerabu, pass!
The Goddess Bowl is a decent leicha. The only complaint is the lukewarm tea soup. Buddha Bowl is sweet and creamy. Zucchini soup not bad.
Interesting orange pork ribs. Has a hint of cumin. Minced pork tofu is very fragrant with deep fried dried shrimp. Lou Sang is in-house with none of those pre-pack crisps.
Great dining atmosphere at Lvl 23A. View of KLCC, KL Tower. Early dinner for good light for food photography. Fuego ceviche and guacamole recommended. Rare beef flank too chewy although medium rare.

formattedAddress: Level 23A, Tower B, The Troika (Jalan Binjai)
50450 Kuala Lumpur City Center, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Good pork knuckles in. Creamy sauce. Lou Sang also good. Most of the signature items here go well with a generous helping of white rice.

venue.name: Restoran Makan Laut Zhen Liew Xiang (正留香海鲜楼)

tip.text: Tried their pre-spring kaiseki for RM110. Good for two to share. Had their monthly special of Teri-Otoro at RM29 for 100gms. Yummy tuna. Free valet parking for customers.
Asam black pomfret is fresh and crispy. Rendang pork ribs also thick and aromatic. Wouldn't exactly say it's very homecooked. Hot tong sui available.
Platters are great for sharing, with variety. Comes with loads of yummy Mediterranean rice. Drinks a bit icky though, saw the staff tasting with a spoon and redunking it into the drinks tower again.
Come here for cheap-ish Japanese food with quick service. Come early to secure a table or you might end up with an Al fresco dining experience.

formattedAddress: 4-2, Jalan Telok Gadong (Off Jalan Klang Lama)

tip.text: Morning: Soup noodles. Sliced pork with rice wine, handmade pork balls. Piping hot soup. Recommended. Night: Thai restaurant (still open?). Not recommended.
Nasi Lemak here is cheap and delicious. Sambal is good, but the rice is topped by the stall right outside their doorstep. Menu contains noodles and bread as well. Bihun is quite good. Cham is good!

They've moved upstairs to a bigger space. Renovations are nice. Coffees come in two blends, Driver and Sugar Daddy. Try the Bombshell, a cold brew that has an alcoholic aftertaste although it's halal.

location.address: No. 10, Jalan Anggerik Vanilla M 31/M, Kota Kemuning
formattedAddress: No. 10, Jalan Anggerik Vanilla M 31/M, Kota Kemuning

tip.text: Dim sum costs between 5.50 and 6.50 here. Portions are bigger than usual. Pretty good. I like the Siew mai and mini egg tart. Air-conditioned with hotel parking.
Full sized portion of mussels or clams is 900 gms. Comes in many varieties of flavours. Served with two portions garlic bread or potato wedges. Do try.
Set meal not value for money. And I thought Foong Lye was expensive. Food hardly warm. Lethargic service. Asked for chili twice and it did not come.
The kinilaw is great with rice, a Filipino ceviche. Kalderata chicken tasted like something out of a Chinese restaurant. A very familiar taste for me. The coconut shake comes with vanilla ice cream.
Light and 'fluffy' mee goreng. Salad has a citrus-y dressing that helps cut the oil from all the porky power.

formattedAddress: 2, Jalan 20/70A, Desa Sri Hartamas (Jalan Sri Hartamas 22)

tip.text: Value for money lunch sets at RM19- Bread, main, drink and dessert. The only complaint is the slow service.

contact.facebookName: Doubletree by Hilton Raleigh-Durham Airport at Research Triangle Park

location.address: Lobby Level, DoubleTree by Hilton, Kuala Lumpur
formattedAddress: Lobby Level, DoubleTree by Hilton, Kuala Lumpur (The Intermark, 182 Jalan Tun Razak)

tip.text: 2016/12: YTF is 1.20 per piece. Try the grilled chicken wings and pandan chicken.

formattedAddress: Kuala Lumpur, Federal Territory of Kuala Lum

tip.text: Black Fried Rice is recommended. For an extra kick, order Crispy baby squid to put on top. Tender beef ribs is just like an overly-sweet rendang. Blue Crabmeat pizza is also nice. Thin and crispy.

location.address: Publika (Block C4, Lot 28-29, Level UG), Jalan Dutamas 1
formattedAddress: Publika (Block C4, Lot 28-29, Level UG), Jalan Dutamas 1

tip.text: Couldn't really detect the salted egg in the salted egg pasta. Curry leaf aroma covered it all? Portions are generous here. Love the white affogatto.
Beef Carpaccio was very fruity with mango,blueberries, pomegranate, and strawberries. Unfortunately, the beef itself was kinda bland. Halibut and clams was quite good, but comes with no carbs.

formattedAddress: Level 1 Menara Naza, Platinum Park (Persiaran KLCC)

tip.text: Decent ramen. Soup not too thick. Two of us shared the Tonkotsu King and we were stuffed! 1.5 noodles portion, charsiu, chicken charsiu, ajitama, vegetables, seaweed and Bamboo shoots.

location.address: Atria shopping gallery jalan SS  22/23，damansara jaya
formattedAddress: Atria shopping gallery jalan SS  22/23，damansara jaya

tip.text: Good Indonesian food here. Try the bebek penyet and mie goreng iga.  Good beef. The chili is amazing! Love the decor with all the colorful recycled old wood.
Peranakan food here, cincalok omelette, kapitan curry chicken, terung balado. Good use of spices. But the chicken was kinda 'reput'. Kopi here is decent.
The theme here is pseudo LOTR. Similar but different. You get a Hobbit home backdrop where you can put on elf ears, a floppy gray hat, hobbit feet or a battle axe. They have savoury waffles here.
The Owls Cafe branch with much more seating, space and plenty of natural light. Same menu I suppose.

contact.facebookName: New Chapter by The Owls Cafe

location.address: Calvary Convention Centre, Jalan Jalil Perkasa 1
formattedAddress: Calvary Convention Centre, Jalan Jalil Perkasa 1

venue.name: New Chapter by The Owls Café

tip.text: Portions on the menu look bigger than the real thing, do the prices are a little steep. Taste-wise not bad. They serve PORK here.
I love the hojicha ice cream. Great aroma and not too sweet.

formattedAddress: 55100 Kuala Lumpur Pusat Bandar, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Great place for a cup of coffee. Have a coffee outside or on the balcony. B1F1 coffee from 0800 till 1000. Sandwiches from Tommy Le Baker are available, and Nasi Lemak bungkus.
Go for the express lunch sets. Coffee pork ribs didn't really taste of coffee but it's tender and the sauce is reducted nicely. Pork burger comes with bacon and a thick, juicy patty. Filling.
Curry Frank is very fragrant using minced lamb, black eyes peas and various spices. The frankfurter is chicken. The bun is homemade and soft and fluffy. Goes well with a cup of siphon Haikara coffee.
Roti Jala is soft and hot. Curry chicken that comes with it is creamy and not too spicy. Chicken meat has some bite. Recommended. Assam laksa is quite spicy. Dunno why, but my coffee was too bitter.

formattedAddress: 1 Utama Shopping Centre (LG320-LG320A, 1 Lebuh Bandar Utama)

tip.text: Le Lapin's replacement. Coffee, flower teas, mains and snacks. They serve pork here. Rolls, rice, burgers and pasta.
A place for expensive Malay food, but I have no complaints about the quality. The fried chicken and oxtail in the Serai Platter are delish. The rendang tok from the Nasi campur is also recommended.
Curry Noodles here is not the creamy type. Very full of spice and fragrant herbs. Service is very fast. They even give you extra soup. CKT here is also decent. Forget about the asam laksa.
Typical flea market with full selection of fruits, vegetables, meat, seafood, flowers and dry groceries. Public toilet there charges RM0.50 though.
The mango shake shake ice is quite good. A sorbet-like dessert that tastes of much natural fruit. Their rojak is also made with a thick gravy of shrimp sauce.
Rojak with a long history. Comes with jicama, jambu air, squid in lye water, Prawn crackers, kangkung, bean sprouts, mango, cucumber. If you order coconut water, do ask them to hold the sugar.
Minimalist design, quiet place for single origins coffee and fine teas. The beetroot choc cake is moist and yummy.
UOB credit card promotion till 2017/07. Buy one, free one coffees. Flat white is decent. RM10 nett.
Wholemeal Toast is a lovely combo of hash Brown and sunny side up. Cute breakfast place in a most unexpected place.
Surprisingly the ice-blended green tea latte is nice, not sickly sweet or too milky. Try to avoid sitting near the kitchen, it perpetually smells over heated oil over there.
Beautiful interior and even more beautiful food presentation. Very meticulous. We tried the Juliet, matcha kanten, key lime pie, choc rose sandwich, all of which were good and well balanced.
A shop that specialises in dry kampua noodles. Charsiew is a bit dark but quite good. Noodles I find a bit sticky, but it's OK. They also have a mee goreng mamak for stronger tastebuds.
Lam Mee's homemade ramen has good texture, however the gravy is way too sweet. When we gave our feedback, the waitress actually thanked us and told the owner. The curry mee is quite nice, hot!

venue.name: Uncle Xian Noodles House 阿贤猪肉丸拉面馆

tip.text: Fantastic ambience. Love the interior. Mixed grill platter is great for sharing. Succulent and tender cuts. The duck jamon didn't leave much of an impression though.

location.address: Ground Floor, Suasana Bukit Ceylon, 2, Persiaran Raja Chulan,
formattedAddress: Ground Floor, Suasana Bukit Ceylon, 2, Persiaran Raja Chulan,

tip.text: 3 cups chicken full of sweet basil. Nice. Red wine mee suah also got standard. Their mixed vegetables tofu also Yummy. Big portions. Tong sui is average.
The menu describes the Thigh & Mighty burger as something with two pieces of chicken thigh. This burger costs RM22. The reality is a small piece of chicken thigh cut into two. Rip off.
In the photo is a two person portion of bean sprout chicken (kampung). Huge. MYR 17 with one portion of white rice.
Branch of the YTF at Puchong Batu 14. The fish paste has a good texture. They also have dishes like steamed fish, superior soup chicken, etc. YTF is RM1.50 per piece.

location.address: 21, Jln PSK 2, Pusat Perdagangan Seri Kembangan
formattedAddress: 21, Jln PSK 2, Pusat Perdagangan Seri Kembangan

tip.text: Nasi Kerabu is pretty good, but they serve it with a very creamy gravy that I'm not quite used to. The Nasi Dagang didn't taste right and the rice was too soft. Missing the halba? Capital's is better

location.address: F-45-G, Jalan PJU 1/45, Aman Suria Damansara
formattedAddress: F-45-G, Jalan PJU 1/45, Aman Suria Damansara

tip.text: Specialty desserts. The choices are diverse enough that they should fit a wide palette. Prices range from RM22. Attentive service, very friendly. Nicely decorated interior. Crispy profiteroles FTW!

formattedAddress: 60000 Taman Tun Dr Ismail, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Sang har meen is RM45 per portion, that's 1.5 big prawns. Lovely gravy. Fresh. Try the pork ribs too. Lala not quite to my taste. There's also salted egg bitter gourd sang meen.

location.address: 33, Jalan SR 8/4, Taman Putra Indah, Serdang Raya
formattedAddress: 33, Jalan SR 8/4, Taman Putra Indah, Serdang Raya (Taman Putra Indah, Serdang Raya)

tip.text: Many people come here to catch the sunset. Try to beat the crowds to set up your camera for the best view of KL Tower and KLCC. Cocktails are RM30 AM and you need a drink to access the helipad.
Cheap at RM3 per plate but portions are smaller and not very good. My biggest complaint would be the skin, soggy and soft.
The Ferrero Rocher cake is quite good, better than the naked red velvet. I like the iced latte.
Signature dish is the dry loh c fun. Don't mistake it for the short noodles that KL-ites are used to. It's like Lai Fun. Pork oil aplenty here. Hakka Mee and Wantan Mee is good too.
Excellent oyster omelette. Fluffy and fresh. The fried is bihun has a good texture, but kinda oily in my opinion.

location.address: No 16, Jalan 1/109E, Desa Business Park, Taman Desa
formattedAddress: No 16, Jalan 1/109E, Desa Business Park, Taman Desa

tip.text: Try the Lai Fun, great rice noodles texture, but the minced meat is kinda salt. Also try the sotong bihun, something quite unique. Forget about the Hakka noodles. Sticky and tastes of boric acid.
Two floors of coffee, bingsu and cake. Coffee is OK, but no latte art here.

formattedAddress: No. 297, Jalan S2 B13, (Uptown Avenue, Seremban 2)

tip.text: Order 1.5 portions and you probably can feed 3 pax. Seafood is fresh. Not exactly teochew porridge, more like rice in broth. Like at Go Rice Shop.
Pho Bo's soup is pretty sweet, but the kway teow used is nice. The beef balls are made in-house, pretty good. Prices are fair. Manned by Vietnamese.
An uncommon sight to see a baked chicken leg topped with cheese on spaghetti. But at 23.90, it really hits the spot. The calzone is a little tasteless, put more sauce on it.
Signature Hoagie is spicy. Meat slice is quite meager.
Keyword here is halal ramen. Soup base is chicken and the charsiu is replaced with chicken. Truth be told, the soup is hot and clear. Noodles also have a good texture and the ajitama passes the test.

formattedAddress: Level 5, NU Sentral Mall (Jalan Tun Sambanthan)

tip.text: Great service here, perfect for dates. Food is also great. They have a good six-course meal for SGD78++ with a good selection. Meats and seafoods are equally good.
Meatballs are great, with some crisp on the outside and good texture on the inside. Goes well with the jam and sauce, but the potatoes are a bit bland. The beef sautéed with onions is also delicious.

formattedAddress: #02-K3, OneKM Shopping Mall (11 Tanjong Katong Rd.)

tip.text: A good mix of savoury food and desserts. Softserve ice cream + green tea ice cream + kanten jelly + mochi + azuki is recommended.
Rosti is pretty good, but gets a bit chewy when cold. The poached eggs are cold and tasteless which is strange. Love the flat white. And good for kids cause there's a bouncy castle and kids soccer.

formattedAddress: Block N #01-56 Goodman Arts Centre (90 Goodman Road)

tip.text: Go try the fried noodles at stall 406/407. Yummy.
Very nice place to chill with a cup of coffee. Even the smoking area is well-decorated and cosy. Do try the lemon cheese cake.
This taoist temple is dedicated to the Heavenly Mother and is located on Robson Heights, an elevated piece of land where you can get a view of the nearby areas.
Salad with salmon sashimi, ikura and salmon skin. Good mixture.
Huge floor space with a small selection of coffee and cakes. And of course a pop-up store of local art.
Wouldn't say that the roast duck is excellent, but the roast pork is worth a mention. I like the YTF. Not filled with fish paste, but minced pork of good texture. Fast service.
The Carnivorous Pizza is highly-recommended. Salad portions are small. Service is good when they aren't too swamped.

location.address: Glo Damansara Mall No., 699, Jalan Damansara, Taman Tun Dr Ismail
formattedAddress: Glo Damansara Mall No., 699, Jalan Damansara, Taman Tun Dr Ismail (Jalan Damansara)

tip.text: Overpriced Malaysian food at average quality and taste. Ever tried apam balik with peanut butter, chocolate sauce and ice cream?
Coffee, waffles and Asian food. Not premium waffles, but at least folks in Kinrara have an option. Opening tea time special: each waffle order comes with a free drink. Each Asian dish is 20% off.
Surprisingly the baked pork bun is yummy. Chunky filling, good taste. Ice bath milk tea is too sweet.
Steamed chicken bihun is quite different, with loads of ginger, garlic and yellow wine. Also go for the stuffed tofupok and homemade tofu.
Shore to Please is a great fresh seafood crepe brought together with a yummy hamtan sauce. Affogato is great too, love the 'garnishing'.

Tried the cendol, but it doesn't really taste like cendol. The roti jala has good texture, but the curry chicken is too oily and the meat too soft. Kuih has similar size and pricing like Nyonya Colors
I love their signature Tea Verandah mix. Very fruity. Good combo. Avoid their pasta, too soggy.

formattedAddress: SK1 Level 2, ATRIA Shopping Gallery (Jalan SS 22/23, Damansara Jaya)

tip.text: Nothing to shout about. Manhattan is a combination of waffle fries, cheese, steak, onions. Quite nice.
RM2 for hamachi sushi. Sushi rice not cooked well. Overall price is cheaper than average.
I've been told that the charsiew here is excellent, but I find it average. Curry noodles is quite watery. Nothing to shout about.

venue.name: 金记好好食云吞面家 Good Taste Restaurant

tip.text: Excellent HK yuan yang. The mui choi pork rice is also good. The snow skin pork bun is too sweet.

venue.name: Hong Kong Sheng Kee Dessert 香港盛记甜品

tip.text: Butter croissant - 5.90Peach Melba - 3.90Bluberry Twist - 3.90Flat white is decent.
Love the carbonara. Semi-dry style. The cold salmon is also great.
Mee kolok and a cup of iced kopi c for lunch. Satisfying.
Recommended the signature coffee, matcha-passionfruit mille crepe and red velvet (natural beetroot). Attentive service.

formattedAddress: Lot UG26, Empire Shopping Gallery (Jalan SS16/1)

tip.text: Sets come with a main, 4 pieces of YTF and drinks. Average taste.

venue.name: Restoran Ipoh Big Tree Noodle 怡保大树脚料面

tip.text: The place for cheap ramen. Used to be cheaper but everything is more expensive now. Beware, their floor is very oily and slippery!
Good atmosphere, good price. That's about it. Chaotic service, pacing of the food is horrible. Kitchen missed my order and I was only the second table for dinner. Avoid.
Black Forest coffee jelly frappe is not bad. Not too artificial. On offer at MYR7.

Tried the shio toro chasiu. As you can see, lots of meat, but I didn't really like the texture. Noodles and broth are OK.

tip.text: The pork ribs are superb, so juicy and tender. Subtlely flavoured with brandy and soy sauce. The Furano Dama okonomiyaki is also a specialty and is suitable for potato lovers.

venue.name: Teppan Okonomiyaki Masaya (てっぱん・お好み焼 まさ屋)

tip.text: Try the new double sausage and egg McMuffin with bacon! Yummy!

venue.name: マクドナルド 38号富良野店

tip.text: This family-run place has eight cottages decorated predominatly with a wooden theme. There is also a restaurant that serves a killer black vegetable curry.
They have a free artificial hot spring feature and two free parking lots. Many restaurants are located a stone's throw away.

venue.name: Natulux Hotel Furano (富良野 ナチュラクス ホテル)

tip.text: 40 sculptures by Ken Yasuda. Free entrance. Beautiful surroundings. A fantastic way to while away the afternoon.

venue.name: ARTE PIAZZA BIBAI   アルテピアッツァ美唄

tip.text: Sarawak Laksa comes with a good measure of spices. Soup is piping hot and the noodles have a good texture. Service is friendly, place is clean.
Long queue. Fat stick. Moist. The nasi padat is nice. Wrapped in leaf like Indonesian lontong. Beware of bad traffic.
Set: main + lemon tea + fruit is around MYR13. The wantan mee they use is very springy and thin. They serve the food piping hot, which I like.
Love the salad with duck gizzard and croutons. Delicious!
Not exactly worth queueing for. Buy during off peak periods.
Chocolate walnut macchiato cake is recommended. Coffee is also decent.
Red Riding Hood for Strawberry lovers. Not exactly the fluffy type, more crispy. Lots of flavoured coffees like rose, lavender, etc
Anna's salad wrap is interesting as it features a stack of wide kway teow. I love it.

formattedAddress: Lot 08, Level G - Boulevard, Paradigm Mall (Lot GB-08, Level G Boulevard)

tip.text: Lovely moist carrot cake. Opening special 30% off. Single origins + RM2.
Such lovely mashed potatoes! So fragrant!
Try the pork chop on a bed of mash with vegetables. The poached egg with vegetables is also delicious.
Central location, right beside the crowded Apolo Theater. Rooms are showing its age.

formattedAddress: Avinguda del Paral·lel, 57 59 (Carrer Nou de la Ramblas)

tip.text: Fish stew in Nazaré style is a satisfying meal with lots of fish meat, bell peppers and potatoes.
Must try the grilled chicken here. Moist and delicious!
Clean rooms and good location. Walking distance from the basilica.
The restaurant serves hot food e.g. Codfish with potatoes and pumpkin soup.
The Ladies Set may not look like much from the picture but it sure packs a punch- appetiser, salad, chawanmushi, miso soup, sashimi, braised pork belly, chirashi don and udon. All for RM55.
Long pork ribs in special sauce is like Dong Po meat. Quite delicious and the fat melts in your mouth.
Surprisingly big portions for their single meal noodles. Ranges from 7.50 to 9.00. Decent taste.
Decent mixed pork soup. They also have wantan mee, curry mee, dishes with steamed rice, yam rice and YTF.

venue.name: 良记家乡美食 Leong Kee Hometown Cuisine

tip.text: Patty is quite tasteless.  Shoestring fries are quite crispy though. Customisation + slow assembly = long queue!
Curry mee is average. No particular fragrance of spices. The sweet and sour pork has much fat in the pieces.

contact.facebookName: Teo Chew Yuen - Fine Teo Chew Cuisine

tip.text: Good place for teh tarik and vadai.
Chicken confit with mashed potatoes. Mashed potatoes tak pass. The chicken meat is kinda reput. Kopi boleh tahan.
Kurobuta katsu is crispy on the outside and moist on the I side. Good texture. The sauce is also nice.

tip.text: Limited choices for breakfast: fried rice and roti jala with a choice of kapitan curry chicken or dhal. Teh tarik and coffee are the machine dispensed stuff. Full menu starts at lunch.
Teh tarik is not bad. Maggi goreng is dry enough but they use too much of the MSG. Fried chicken is moist. Service needs some improvement though.
Pomegranate red velvet is divine!
